					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That seems like a reasonable plan.
<br />
<br />Anyway, unlike modern processors the 6502 prefers structures-of-arrays rather to arrays-of-structures. For the most part at least.
<br />This means that you'd store those meta-tile definitions (for instance) as separate arrays for the collision type, color attributes, component tiles, etc. Even to the point of splitting up 16-bit fields into separate arrays for the high and low bytes. That way you can index the fields of up to 256 meta-tiles directly without 16-bit pointer arithmetic.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

