					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh yeah, sorry, I was forgetting precision bits. In my game, I'll also be using 24-bit coords: 8 High (defines which screen it's on), 8 Low (defines pixel it's on) 8 precision. Precision bits are essential in a platformer, because without them, you can only move something at an integer number of pixels a frame. If you use precision bits, you can move like 1.5 pixels a frame, which really makes a huge difference. It's also important for things like gravity and acceleration/deceleration.
<br />
<br />But you don't have to use AS MANY bits for coords was really what I meant to say.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
